---
name: Offline Playback
description: IndexedDB caching, single-audio guard, offline-first lyrics + karaoke, timeouts to prevent forever-loading
type: feature
---
Offline cache (IndexedDB store `cachedAudio`) bundles per track:
- audioBlob (MP3)
- syncedLyrics, plainLyrics
- karaokeData, karaokeEnabled, lyricsSpeed, bounceIntensity

Player rules:
- Single active audio element enforced via `loadTokenRef` + `stopCurrentSource()` in PlayerContext. Rapid play clicks must never duplicate audio.
- Audio resolution priority: IndexedDB cached blob > local audioFiles store > remote `audio_url` (only when `navigator.onLine`, with 4s lookup timeout + 8s fetch timeout) > YouTube IFrame fallback.
- `loadCachedOrRemoteAudio` accepts a token; stale loads abort silently.

Lyrics + karaoke offline:
- LyricsView always tries `getCachedLyrics` + `getCachedKaraoke` FIRST.
- When offline AND cache hit, skip all Supabase/lyrics.ovh fetches.
- Online path wraps `fetchMergedSongRecord` and `fetchSyncedLyrics` in 4s/6s timeouts to prevent infinite loading.
- Cached karaoke restores: words, early_appearance, mobile_char_limit, lyrics_speed, bounce_intensity.

Lossless badge:
- Shown below the playback control row (NOT under the time row), 12px UPPERCASE, semibold, with `Disc3` icon — same on desktop and mobile.
